WEBVTT

00:04.994 --> 00:06.215
Hey, this is Stephen Furtick.

00:06.255 --> 00:09.358
I'm the pastor of Elevation Church, and this is our podcast.

00:09.478 --> 00:13.982
Be sure to subscribe so we can get you these new sermons every week.

00:14.002 --> 00:14.943
Hope you're blessed today.

00:21.189 --> 00:25.994
Let's give a warm welcome to our entire church family at all of our campuses and online.

00:26.955 --> 00:28.156
Hey, welcome, EFAM.

00:32.300 --> 00:34.802
I haven't done an EFAM roll call in a while.

00:34.946 --> 00:39.793
name and where you're watching from please in the chat if you're watching online.

00:40.634 --> 00:43.998
And everybody in this place today, be encouraged.

00:44.699 --> 00:46.101
The Lord has heard your prayers.

00:48.304 --> 00:49.646
The Lord has heard your prayers.

00:50.307 --> 00:51.909
Tell the person next to you he heard you.

00:53.271 --> 00:55.394
Tell him just cause he didn't do it like you wanted him to.

00:55.454 --> 00:56.515
Doesn't mean he didn't hear you.

00:59.760 --> 01:04.466
We were singing a song a moment ago called, call God and we said, I call God and he answered.

01:05.346 --> 01:07.308
And some people were like, well, he hadn't yet.

01:07.609 --> 01:09.271
I wish he would.

01:09.431 --> 01:12.835
But the thing is, he did so many times before.

01:14.217 --> 01:15.418
So many times before.

01:15.438 --> 01:25.931
And I'm going to preach a little bit about this today, but sometimes we adapt to our answered prayers and we cease to appreciate them.

01:25.951 --> 01:35.122
But one thing I'm going to be very intentional about from this pulpit in this year is to not let you just walk past stuff that God did in your life without recognizing it.

01:36.034 --> 01:37.856
Because that's how the enemy weakens you.

01:37.896 --> 01:46.886
So you're going to notice me a lot more in my sermons than when I come up just turning your attention not only to the things that God has done, but who He is.

01:48.088 --> 01:49.689
Because that's what you can count on.

01:50.871 --> 01:53.874
If your wife divorces you, he'll never leave you or forsake you.

01:54.575 --> 02:01.042
If your kids go absolutely prodigal crazy, God is still going to keep you in your right mind.

02:01.826 --> 02:07.611
If everybody in your company gets together and votes you off the island, God will take care of you.

02:08.012 --> 02:10.874
He will supply your needs.

02:10.894 --> 02:16.580
So I want to connect you today through a Scripture in Joshua chapter 17.

02:16.620 --> 02:18.161
And let's do a shout out real quick.

02:18.181 --> 02:24.587
I told the people online, hello from Kenya, hello from West Virginia.

02:24.627 --> 02:31.794
Now how would you feel if you were me if you had to preach a message that applied in Kenya and West Virginia, all in English today?

02:32.802 --> 02:34.024
We're glad to have you.

02:34.365 --> 02:36.408
What a robust church we are.

02:37.410 --> 02:38.010
I love it.

02:38.191 --> 02:38.712
I love it.

02:39.152 --> 02:40.394
Welcome Dayton, Ohio.

02:40.434 --> 02:41.717
Welcome California.

02:42.959 --> 02:46.705
Welcome Cape Town.

02:51.132 --> 02:52.654
Welcome Cornelius, North Carolina.

02:52.674 --> 02:53.696
Well, you should be in church.

02:53.756 --> 02:56.040
You shouldn't be watching.

02:56.060 --> 02:57.362
You just told on yourself.

02:59.522 --> 03:00.804
I'm glad you're here today.

03:00.864 --> 03:01.264
Welcome.

03:01.344 --> 03:01.805
Settle in.

03:01.885 --> 03:02.946
God has a word for you.

03:05.609 --> 03:07.151
Joshua chapter 17.

03:08.793 --> 03:12.878
You ever notice you don't hear many sermons passed around Joshua chapter three or four?

03:14.821 --> 03:18.305
All the exciting stuff happens kind of in the beginning of the book of Joshua.

03:18.325 --> 03:25.714
They're taking the land and they're, you know, they're going forward in the promise of God and crossing the Jordan.

03:26.178 --> 03:27.580
So we usually preach from that.

03:27.600 --> 03:30.064
Well, I'm going all the way to Joshua 17 today.

03:30.104 --> 03:31.245
See what happens after that.

03:32.207 --> 03:35.251
Now listen to this, because this is where we live in our everyday life.

03:35.271 --> 03:40.558
Everyday life is not always exciting new adventures and explorations on the opportunities that await you.

03:41.239 --> 03:43.583
Sometimes it's just three Advil and a prayer.

03:44.424 --> 03:47.088
And sorry, I'm five minutes late, but I'm here anyway.

03:47.609 --> 03:54.258
And we're trying to deal with that this year, because I preached to you last week that there will always be wheat.

03:54.594 --> 03:58.922
And there will always be weeds in the garden of your life with God.

03:59.704 --> 04:14.292
And I was trying to get you to watch the wheat, not just the weeds, not just looking at the things you can't control and wishing they weren't there, but realizing that what God planted in you is significant in every season of your life, whether you can see the growth or not.

04:15.375 --> 04:17.138
Now in Joshua chapter 17,

04:17.762 --> 04:21.967
something interesting happens and I'll read it and then we'll back into the context.

04:22.027 --> 04:22.808
But listen to this.

04:22.848 --> 04:32.740
The people of Joseph said to Joshua, why have you given us only one allotment and one portion for an inheritance?

04:33.862 --> 04:47.218
Remember they possessed the land that God swore to Abraham and Isaac and Jacob and they got in the land and they won the victory and the people of Joseph, one of the groups

04:47.522 --> 04:52.308
from the nation comes to Joshua the leader and says, why did you only give us one allotment?

04:53.289 --> 04:58.636
Look, we are a numerous people, and the Lord has blessed us abundantly.

04:59.257 --> 05:01.460
Now watch Joshua's response.

05:01.480 --> 05:16.178
If you are so numerous, Joshua answered, since you're so blessed like you say you are, and if the hill country of Ephraim is too small for you, go up into the forest and clear land for yourselves there

05:16.386 --> 05:19.391
in the land of the parasites and the refites.

05:19.491 --> 05:20.372
Those are their enemies.

05:21.554 --> 05:25.720
And the people of Joseph replied, the hill country is not enough for us.

05:26.642 --> 05:35.936
And all the Canaanites who live in the plain have chariots fitted with iron, both those in Bethshaun and its settlements and those in the valley of Jezreel.

05:36.817 --> 05:45.330
But Joshua was said to the tribes of Joseph, to Ephraim and Manasseh, to Ephraim and Manasseh.

05:46.146 --> 05:49.149
You are numerous and very powerful.

05:50.090 --> 05:55.976
You will have not only one allotment, but the forested hill country as well.

05:56.716 --> 05:57.798
Now, lean into this.

05:58.418 --> 06:02.682
Clear it, and its farthest limits will be yours.

06:03.663 --> 06:14.354
Though the Canaanites have chariots fitted with iron, and though they are strong, you can drive them out.

06:15.586 --> 06:17.789
Thank the Lord for his Word one time, would you?

06:18.711 --> 06:20.393
Come on right there, thanking for his Word.

06:23.898 --> 06:26.902
My message today is called, Don't Forget Where You Come From.

06:26.962 --> 06:30.427
Look at three people say, Don't Forget Where You Come From.

06:30.487 --> 06:32.951
Amen.

06:32.971 --> 06:33.732
You may be seated.

06:35.955 --> 06:37.237
Don't Forget Where You Come From.

06:37.377 --> 06:38.779
Kenya or West Virginia?

06:40.302 --> 06:43.346
Or like me, maybe you came from Monks Corner, South Carolina.

06:44.930 --> 06:46.853
Boy, somebody said something to me the other day.

06:46.933 --> 06:47.895
I never thought I'd hear.

06:47.955 --> 06:50.679
They said the traffic is terrible in Monks Corner.

06:52.802 --> 06:54.585
It's changed a lot since I was there.

06:55.466 --> 07:01.496
Bad traffic in Monks Corner when I was a boy meant you had to wait through the red light once at rush hour.

07:02.597 --> 07:03.659
But I guess it's growing.

07:03.679 --> 07:05.342
You know, it's really expanding.

07:05.442 --> 07:05.943
And it is.

07:06.063 --> 07:06.403
It is.

07:06.624 --> 07:06.944
It is.

07:07.625 --> 07:09.308
It's all the population that's pushed in.

07:09.348 --> 07:13.234
Anyway, I won't tell you the geography of Charleston and the low country of South Carolina.

07:13.442 --> 07:16.526
By the way, welcome our newest campus in Somerville, South Carolina.

07:17.968 --> 07:21.352
And y'all know I love Jesus because Somerville was our rival in high school.

07:21.612 --> 07:24.796
We were the Berkeley stags and we hated the Somerville green wave.

07:24.816 --> 07:29.842
And now God has prepared a table in the presence of my enemies in Somerville, South Carolina.

07:30.243 --> 07:30.924
But we love you.

07:30.964 --> 07:33.487
No, no.

07:33.527 --> 07:39.314
The reason I bring up where you come from is because everybody in here has a point of reference.

07:39.810 --> 07:43.635
For what you think is successful in your life, you have a point of reference.

07:44.736 --> 07:50.444
If you never had $500 in your bank account before, the first 500 feels amazing.

07:51.525 --> 07:52.467
It's a point of reference.

07:54.069 --> 08:04.522
If you're 73 years old and hoping to retire next year, $500… There's not a prayer warrior in the world that can turn $500 into a retirement account, but it's your point of reference.

08:04.883 --> 08:07.346
I remember the first bonus I got.

08:07.746 --> 08:10.048
when I was working at a church in Shelby, North Carolina.

08:10.969 --> 08:16.996
Rick Boling told me, by the way, we're giving a $500 bonus to all of our employees this Christmas.

08:18.097 --> 08:19.038
I literally cried.

08:19.058 --> 08:24.423
22-year-old, 23-year-old men just crying over $500.

08:25.024 --> 08:34.834
Sometimes I wish I could still cry that easy, because there was something about that stage in my life where I wasn't expecting a bonus.

08:35.394 --> 08:41.944
I remember when he first sat me down and explained my salary package to me, he was like, um, this is how much we're going to pay you this year.

08:42.324 --> 08:45.529
And of course that doesn't include the benefits.

08:45.549 --> 08:46.370
And I said, the what?

08:47.772 --> 08:48.694
He said the benefits.

08:48.714 --> 08:51.337
And this is how in school I was because my dad was self-employed.

08:51.698 --> 08:53.661
I didn't even know what benefits were.

08:53.841 --> 08:59.449
I didn't know that that's something that you could negotiate into a, so I wasn't negotiating.

08:59.530 --> 09:00.451
I was just thankful.

09:00.511 --> 09:02.033
I was like benefits.

09:02.073 --> 09:05.298
He's like, yeah, the benefits, that's, that's going to be additional to this amount.

09:06.946 --> 09:12.996
It's been a while since I praised God for my health insurance, because I had it too long.

09:17.844 --> 09:26.578
Sometimes I let three days go by and don't tell Holly how pretty she is, but that's wrong, because she's pretty every day, and she deserves to be told that every day.

09:27.740 --> 09:31.506
Plus, I spend too much on those clothes she's wearing, not to compliment how she looks.

09:32.290 --> 09:43.242
and that $280 makeup that's in her bathroom, whatever I'm spending over there at Sephora, I feel like she deserves to hear it.

09:43.482 --> 09:45.784
When we were dating, it was just constantly every day.

09:45.824 --> 09:58.898
But one thing I noticed in the text that we read is that when you forget how far you've come from a certain point, it makes how far you have to go the only thing that you're focused on.

09:59.906 --> 10:08.137
And when you forget the gifts that God has given you, it makes it impossible for you to access the power that he put inside of you.

10:08.157 --> 10:09.299
Don't forget where you come from.

10:10.360 --> 10:14.145
Don't forget that there was a time that a $500 Christmas bonus made you cry.

10:15.186 --> 10:27.643
Don't forget that there was a time when you prayed that God would give you these children, that you're praying for him to help you not to eliminate from the face of the earth at this very moment.

10:28.684 --> 10:29.906
Don't forget where you come from.

10:31.842 --> 10:39.671
We see an interesting dynamic in Joshua chapter 17 in that these tribes, the people of Joseph, it's actually two tribes.

10:39.891 --> 10:41.933
One is called Manasseh and one is called Ephraim.

10:41.993 --> 10:43.155
Those were Joseph's boys.

10:43.695 --> 10:58.512
Manasseh was his firstborn, Ephraim was his second, and both of them were born in Egypt in the place where he suffered, in the place where he was falsely accused, in the place where he was thrown into prison, in the place where God also raised him to prominence in Egypt.

10:58.532 --> 11:00.754
He had two boys, Manasseh,

11:01.314 --> 11:02.936
and Ephraim.

11:02.956 --> 11:07.601
And those boys have now, several generations later, turned into tribes.

11:08.422 --> 11:11.386
And these tribes have taken territory in the land of Canaan.

11:12.287 --> 11:19.676
And not only have they settled into the land, but they've started to grow and do what people do, you know, when two people love each other very much.

11:19.996 --> 11:20.677
So they've grown.

11:20.717 --> 11:22.919
I have to talk with you later.

11:23.420 --> 11:28.466
It's just that they're blessed so much.

11:29.154 --> 11:32.638
that they are experiencing the pressure of blessing.

11:34.960 --> 11:46.873
Many times in church we only speak to the desperation of failure, but there is a need to preach to the pressure of blessings because blessings are heavy in your life.

11:48.374 --> 11:55.602
Sometimes when you're going through all of the things you're worried about, it's not even so much that you're complaining about them or that you don't appreciate them.

11:56.098 --> 12:00.885
It's that pressure has kept your perspective from seeing the bigger picture of what's happening.

12:01.787 --> 12:04.030
So you get zoned in on only one thing.

12:04.851 --> 12:12.303
And you forget, like the tribes of Ephraim and Manasseh, that just a few years ago, you were wandering in the wilderness.

12:13.144 --> 12:16.048
That's kind of why when I read this Scripture, it stood out to me.

12:16.629 --> 12:21.416
Because when I read it, I wanted to say to them, you just left the wilderness.

12:22.338 --> 12:25.202
And now you're complaining that there's not enough room for you.

12:25.858 --> 12:27.479
Did you notice what they said to Joshua?

12:27.820 --> 12:29.962
Why did you only give us one allotment?

12:29.982 --> 12:31.803
We're too big for this place.

12:31.823 --> 12:33.104
We need more elbow room.

12:33.405 --> 12:34.746
We need new countertops.

12:35.146 --> 12:36.607
We need hardwood floors.

12:37.368 --> 12:39.170
We need more space.

12:39.190 --> 12:40.271
We need a minivan.

12:40.771 --> 12:42.673
We're a growing nation.

12:43.633 --> 12:45.335
It's getting bigger in Monks Corner.

12:45.635 --> 12:47.877
The traffic is terrible in Monks Corner.

12:48.297 --> 12:55.844
Everything in the text is growing, and while everything is growing, their perspective is narrowing, and all they can see is the

12:55.824 --> 13:25.796
that they don't have and so they come to Joshua and the people of Joseph in Genesis or excuse me in Joshua chapter 17 verse 14 say why have you only given us one allotment we're innumerous people and the Lord has blessed us abundantly but just because he blessed us doesn't mean we don't have pressure just because I have money doesn't mean I know how to manage it just because God gave me a job doesn't mean I don't get tired

13:25.776 --> 13:31.842
Just because God sent people to my ministry doesn't mean I always have a message to give them when they show up.

13:32.543 --> 13:34.165
Blessings create pressure.

13:34.205 --> 13:38.329
If pressure is not dealt with, pressure can create self-pity.

13:38.669 --> 13:47.038
Self-pity, if not dealt with, can create a situation where you are in this state of, watch this, too much and not enough.

13:47.058 --> 13:48.800
That's what they said in verse 16.

13:49.120 --> 13:51.702
They said, we do not have enough land.

13:52.003 --> 13:55.186
The land that you gave us is not enough.

13:55.362 --> 14:01.071
for us, and the people are too much for the land that is not enough.

14:01.712 --> 14:12.608
I felt like when I studied, I'd be preaching to somebody today who would understand this tension of too much and not enough, too much and not enough.

14:13.369 --> 14:23.004
This is why we toss and turn, because it's too much and not enough, too much to do and not enough in my tank to do it.

14:23.345 --> 14:24.306
That's called burnout.

14:24.994 --> 14:30.241
Too much of people calling me and not enough patience to listen to their problems.

14:31.002 --> 14:36.549
Too much bills and not enough income to answer the bills when they knock at the door.

14:37.270 --> 14:43.157
Too much on my mind and not enough in my life that makes me feel happy and recharged.

14:43.718 --> 14:46.802
Too much demand, not enough supply.

14:46.882 --> 14:51.368
Too many people sucking energy out of me and not enough people supplying it.

14:51.888 --> 14:55.273
Too many people asking and not enough people offering.

14:55.773 --> 14:59.218
Too many things wrong and not enough things working out.

14:59.878 --> 15:02.742
Too much and not enough.

15:04.344 --> 15:05.105
That's what they said.

15:05.546 --> 15:06.307
Look at verse 16.

15:06.327 --> 15:07.088
It's in the Bible.

15:07.929 --> 15:15.378
They said, The land you gave us, verse 16, is not enough.

15:16.898 --> 15:17.499
It's not enough.

15:18.541 --> 15:19.001
All right.

15:19.021 --> 15:20.684
So let's talk about that for a minute.

15:20.704 --> 15:21.365
It's not enough.

15:22.567 --> 15:23.589
I'm not gifted enough.

15:24.570 --> 15:25.752
I'm not talented enough.

15:26.533 --> 15:27.815
I'm not experienced enough.

15:27.995 --> 15:32.803
I told you during the same lies new loop series that the devil only has two lies that he puts on a loop in your mind.

15:33.444 --> 15:35.928
And one is I'm not loved and one is not enough.

15:38.011 --> 15:44.882
So that's why you wake up in the morning feeling like, well, what's on my agenda for today is too much and the time I have to do it in is not enough.

15:46.338 --> 15:48.160
That's what I'm using this land to represent.

15:48.521 --> 15:53.708
If you thought I was going to teach a real estate seminar off of Joshua chapter 17, that's not my expertise.

15:54.649 --> 16:00.296
I'm trying to teach a real life seminar about why you're snapping at the wrong people.

16:03.580 --> 16:10.930
I'm trying to teach a real life seminar about why you don't look forward to some of the stuff that God actually gave you through his favor.

16:12.642 --> 16:17.008
I'm trying to teach a real-life seminar about how you could be so blessed.

16:17.028 --> 16:20.212
Did you notice the tribes, they said, we're so blessed.

16:20.232 --> 16:22.215
And I dare somebody to just say it by faith.

16:22.255 --> 16:25.079
Say, I'm so blessed.

16:25.099 --> 16:25.980
I'm so blessed.

16:26.000 --> 16:26.661
Say it with a head shake.

16:26.681 --> 16:29.705
Say, I am so blessed.

16:29.725 --> 16:32.970
Matter of fact, do this at every campus and especially at Valentine.

16:33.330 --> 16:37.636
Look at the person on either side of you and say, you are so blessed.

16:39.619 --> 16:41.842
Tell them, I am so blessed.

16:42.018 --> 16:43.346
You are so blessed.

16:43.554 --> 16:47.798
Matter of fact, start doing like this because I'm so blessed.

16:47.818 --> 16:49.139
I need some elbow room.

16:49.439 --> 16:51.221
I'm so blessed.

16:51.241 --> 16:53.342
I need you to scoot over a little bit.

16:53.363 --> 16:54.644
I'm so blessed.

16:54.664 --> 16:56.065
You better get out of my way.

16:56.485 --> 17:13.540
I'm so blessed because if I think for a minute about that $500 bonus and how much God has done for me since then, if I think for a minute about how he kept me upright on my feet and in my right mind, you better give me some room because if

17:13.520 --> 17:24.872
I think for one minute about how I called and he answered and he came through like only he could just not your neighbor say we're so blessed.

17:24.892 --> 17:26.734
Getting more blessed every day.

17:26.754 --> 17:30.077
I'm spreading out my tent in this season.

17:30.638 --> 17:35.583
I'm driving down my stakes in this season because I'm so blessed.

17:36.404 --> 17:38.886
That's why I'm tired because God bless me.

17:40.808 --> 17:42.290
What a perspective.

17:43.746 --> 17:46.209
And now the land I have is not enough.

17:46.630 --> 17:51.536
And so now your prayer request is about all your praise reports.

17:53.819 --> 17:56.001
Did that make sense?

17:56.021 --> 17:56.822
I prayed for it.

17:56.982 --> 17:57.463
I got it.

17:57.563 --> 17:58.324
It's a blessing.

17:58.364 --> 17:59.446
It creates pressure.

17:59.686 --> 18:02.209
And the decision in this season of your life is this.

18:02.670 --> 18:04.111
What do I do with the pressure?

18:04.512 --> 18:06.374
What do I do about the not enough?

18:06.795 --> 18:09.458
Why do I feel like it's not enough?

18:09.762 --> 18:17.811
When God sends an opportunity into my life, do I reject it and send it away because I think I can't do it?

18:20.914 --> 18:29.543
Why do I send people who love me away and push people who care about me away and reach for things that destroy me?

18:34.168 --> 18:39.474
Why am I still in this season of my life?

18:40.514 --> 18:46.680
struggling with something that I prayed about since I was a teenager.

18:46.700 --> 18:48.982
Is there not enough of God's power to deliver me?

18:50.404 --> 18:52.246
Do I have not enough faith to receive it?

18:53.227 --> 18:54.188
What's the problem here?

18:55.669 --> 19:04.298
Well, Joshua, Joshua gets a real, I call this a dad energy with these tribes.

19:05.439 --> 19:07.981
See, me and Holly are totally different in our parenting approach.

19:08.021 --> 19:08.722
Totally different.

19:09.218 --> 19:14.925
I told you last week, if my kids run out the house without a coat, I'm like, cool.

19:16.828 --> 19:17.709
She's like, you're going to freeze.

19:17.749 --> 19:18.970
I'm like, they're not going to freeze.

19:19.832 --> 19:23.496
First of all, they're not going to freeze.

19:23.516 --> 19:31.987
Secondly, if they do, it will be a memory in their life that will create maturity for their future.

19:33.649 --> 19:34.871
So I'm just building memories.

19:36.132 --> 19:37.394
I'm building memories.

19:37.570 --> 19:48.503
of the time that your dumb self left without your coat and almost froze to death, and then maybe one day you'll give money to somebody who doesn't have a coat so they can buy one.

19:48.743 --> 19:50.285
So I'm promoting generosity.

19:50.685 --> 19:56.452
I'm teaching you good stewardship and responsibility all by just letting you be an idiot.

19:57.373 --> 19:59.555
The other day Holly was telling me her schedule for the day.

19:59.576 --> 20:00.977
I said, what do you have the rest of the day?

20:01.338 --> 20:03.800
She said, well, all three kids have a dentist appointment.

20:03.840 --> 20:05.202
I said, what does that have to do with you?

20:07.298 --> 20:10.422
I understand Abby, she can't drive yet, but Graham's 18.

20:11.583 --> 20:16.449
Elijah is about to be 21 years old of age in the United States of America.

20:17.570 --> 20:22.617
What does his dentist appointment have to do with you at this stage in your life?

20:23.378 --> 20:25.280
And she's like, if I don't remind them, they'll forget.

20:26.161 --> 20:27.282
And I'm like, and then what?

20:28.544 --> 20:30.907
Well, and then the dentist has to charge me.

20:30.947 --> 20:33.650
And I'm like, but can't you take it out of their account?

20:34.594 --> 20:36.616
And she's like, well, yeah, maybe I guess so.

20:36.696 --> 20:37.777
I didn't think about it like that.

20:37.817 --> 20:52.672
And then I thought, well, if their teeth start falling out, I want you to let enough teeth fall out of their mouth that they don't need you to follow them to the dentist when they're 47 years old.

20:53.012 --> 20:54.333
This is not a good path.

20:54.574 --> 21:02.962
Because if I got to sit in the dentist's office to make sure you're here, you got a beard and I'm taking you to the dentist.

21:05.442 --> 21:07.144
Help me praise the Lord.

21:07.545 --> 21:09.086
All the dads in the house.

21:12.370 --> 21:15.434
Joshua was like, so you want more land?

21:15.554 --> 21:16.455
Now listen, I need to tell you something.

21:16.475 --> 21:17.436
I forgot to tell you this.

21:17.457 --> 21:22.262
The land that they had, it was the second biggest piece given to all of the tribes.

21:22.302 --> 21:23.744
The only one bigger was Judah.

21:25.346 --> 21:28.790
So when they come to Joshua and they're like, Hey, we don't have enough land.

21:28.830 --> 21:31.093
Joshua was like, it's interesting.

21:31.113 --> 21:31.954
You should say that.

21:33.090 --> 21:39.821
because I noticed that when I gave you the land, there were some parts of the land that you did not occupy.

21:41.644 --> 21:47.653
I noticed that when I assigned you the acreage, you had the second biggest plot of land of any of the tribes.

21:48.995 --> 22:00.754
So if you want more room, if you really need more space, instead of asking me for more land, when you've already been given

22:01.058 --> 22:02.800
The second largest piece of land.

22:03.101 --> 22:04.042
Can I stop for a moment?

22:04.322 --> 22:07.707
Somebody else would die to trade places with you in your life.

22:09.429 --> 22:15.037
Somebody else would give all the money in their bank account to have the peace you have in your home.

22:16.199 --> 22:21.646
Somebody else would give their entire career just to have the relationship you have.

22:22.828 --> 22:26.753
It is true that when we are under pressure, we lose perspective.

22:27.734 --> 22:30.578
It is also true that God has given us a lot more.

22:31.042 --> 22:33.687
then we have occupied.

22:33.727 --> 22:48.976
Joshua says, If you are so numerous… Verse 15… And if the hill country of Ephraim, the place where you are, is too small for you… Because when they settled in, some of the land was already developed, because Canaanites were living there.

22:49.818 --> 22:54.226
So when they moved in, they were like, Cool, this is great.

22:54.882 --> 22:59.227
But then after a while all the land that was producing… It was a very fertile piece of land.

22:59.247 --> 22:59.888
Don't get it twisted.

22:59.908 --> 23:01.790
They didn't get any land that was like second rate.

23:01.810 --> 23:02.711
This was not scraps.

23:03.372 --> 23:04.173
This was good land.

23:04.974 --> 23:07.978
But they got in there and they eventually started to outgrow it.

23:08.018 --> 23:11.021
And then they eventually began to grumble because they had grown.

23:11.061 --> 23:13.765
And so they started to grumble about their growth.

23:13.785 --> 23:16.728
And they started to grumble about the gift that God had given.

23:17.009 --> 23:18.971
And you just want to slap them real quick.

23:20.052 --> 23:21.274
Just slap them real quick.

23:21.314 --> 23:21.995
Like, really?

23:22.035 --> 23:24.818
You came from the wilderness.

23:25.922 --> 23:26.343
Really?

23:26.383 --> 23:33.632
God gave you the second largest piece of land, and all you can think of to say is, I want more?

23:33.732 --> 23:34.072
Really?

23:34.112 --> 23:39.079
Sometimes I want to slap myself when I hear the things I complain about.

23:40.320 --> 23:41.181
Here's what I've noticed.

23:42.103 --> 23:54.258
Without a constant focus on the goodness of God, it is easy for me to go from inheritance to entitlement.

23:59.522 --> 24:01.785
Inheritance to entitlement.

24:02.106 --> 24:05.611
Look at this that Paul prayed in Ephesians chapter one.

24:05.871 --> 24:07.073
Put it on the screen, please.

24:07.113 --> 24:23.015
He said, I pray that the eyes of your heart may be enlightened in order that you may know the hope to which he has called you, the riches of his glorious inheritance in his holy people.

24:23.336 --> 24:27.762
So Ephesians is telling us spiritually what Joshua is showing us physically.

24:28.514 --> 24:29.836
that you have an inheritance.

24:30.817 --> 24:43.674
But notice the verse again, put it on the screen for another moment, where he says, I pray that the eyes of your heart may be enlightened to know the riches of the inheritance you already have.

24:44.595 --> 24:46.158
Here is what Paul did not pray.

24:46.518 --> 24:47.319
Check the Scripture.

24:47.960 --> 24:53.387
He did not pray that God would give you an inheritance because you already have one.

24:55.530 --> 24:58.514
What he prayed instead was so specific he said,

24:58.626 --> 25:04.617
I pray that you would be able to see clearly what God has already given you freely.

25:06.420 --> 25:07.602
So this is the shift.

25:08.263 --> 25:10.808
Inheritance says, God gave me this.

25:11.609 --> 25:14.434
God gave me this responsibility to preach today.

25:14.855 --> 25:16.238
I get to do it.

25:16.258 --> 25:18.642
Entitlement says, I've got to do it.

25:19.586 --> 25:25.791
Inheritance says, God has given me the privilege to minister to these precious people.

25:26.232 --> 25:28.274
Y'all don't even know how much I love doing this.

25:28.734 --> 25:30.616
Y'all don't even know how much it matters to me.

25:31.116 --> 25:35.500
Y'all don't even know how much I wake up at 2.30 on Sundays and say, go back to sleep.

25:35.720 --> 25:36.821
You're going to need your energy.

25:37.101 --> 25:41.125
And then it's 2.45, and it's 3.15, and it's 3.30.

25:41.185 --> 25:42.826
And finally say, I can't sleep.

25:43.126 --> 25:45.188
I might as well get up and start thinking about it.

25:45.488 --> 25:49.572
And then by about 3.45, I'm preaching it out loud so I know the kids think that's

25:49.552 --> 25:55.873
He's going crazy downstairs again, but I don't care because God gave me this mantle.

25:56.475 --> 25:57.940
And I'm going to tell you something else.

25:58.381 --> 26:02.354
I prayed hard for this, and I sacrificed for this.

26:02.434 --> 26:04.056
But it wasn't my sacrifice.

26:04.417 --> 26:08.422
It was his sovereignty that gave it to me, because I could not earn this.

26:08.883 --> 26:29.010
And some of us know that it was not by might, and not by power, and not by intelligence, and not by connections, and not by networking, and not by pedigree, and not by GPA, and not by your skill, but by his grace that I am what I am.

26:36.034 --> 26:36.876
Thank you, Lord.

26:38.178 --> 26:38.959
Thank you, God.

26:39.300 --> 26:41.624
Thank you I've got kids to worry about.

26:42.145 --> 26:44.449
Thank you I've got a spouse to fight with.

26:44.990 --> 26:48.537
Thank you I've got clothes to get dirty and have to wash them again.

26:48.577 --> 26:53.225
Thank you I've got dishes to yell at somebody for leaving in the sink.

26:53.245 --> 26:54.567
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

26:54.928 --> 26:58.054
Thank you I've got a toilet to get clogged up.

26:58.074 --> 27:00.498
I remember where I came from.

27:05.570 --> 27:07.632
Slap yourself and say, really?

27:08.533 --> 27:10.135
You're fussing about this?

27:10.795 --> 27:12.777
You forgot where you came from.

27:13.198 --> 27:14.639
You were in a wilderness.

27:14.979 --> 27:16.341
You were in your sin.

27:16.401 --> 27:18.062
You were in chains.

27:18.403 --> 27:19.524
You beg God.

27:19.904 --> 27:23.988
God, if you'll take me, if you'll use me, I'll do anything for you.

27:29.834 --> 27:33.618
And has inheritance mentality.

27:34.114 --> 27:39.260
become entitlement mentality in your life.

27:39.280 --> 27:41.102
Fussing cuz the coffee's cold.

27:42.925 --> 27:45.488
Fussing cuz it buffered for 23 seconds.

27:46.269 --> 27:55.400
Boy, you better remember that card catalog you used to have to go through to find out information, and now you're mad cuz ChatGPT took 12 seconds to think.

27:57.883 --> 28:00.626
Don't forget where you come from.

28:01.730 --> 28:04.032
I come from Monks Corner, South Carolina.

28:05.013 --> 28:15.984
That's why I cannot be discouraged when I stand up in front of large crowds to preach, because when I look at the size of the crowd and realize the town I came from, I'm like, oh, yeah, it was you, God.

28:17.286 --> 28:19.708
I mean, this makes no sense.

28:19.768 --> 28:21.490
This is just absolutely stupid.

28:22.631 --> 28:25.654
I'm so grateful that you used the foolish things of the world that confound the wise.

28:25.694 --> 28:29.458
Now, I need to rush past this point, because I have another point to make.

28:30.690 --> 28:35.317
But maybe this would be a good challenge for you to put in front of your family this week.

28:36.258 --> 28:41.546
Have we allowed inheritance what God gave us to be replaced with entitlement?

28:43.769 --> 28:45.211
Because it's not enough in too much.

28:45.311 --> 28:45.972
Not enough.

28:47.614 --> 28:48.696
You got the blood of Jesus.

28:48.896 --> 28:56.788
One drop of his blood is enough to cleanse you from what you did Thursday.

28:57.388 --> 28:58.450
One drop.

28:58.914 --> 29:05.106
of his blood can erase the shame of how you spent the years between 2020 and 2025.

29:08.071 --> 29:11.698
Holly said they've been sending pictures around online of 2016.

29:12.780 --> 29:17.970
She said, you need to know there's a trend all over Instagram, at least for middle-aged white women.

29:18.210 --> 29:29.044
Everybody's sending around pictures of 2016 and something like 2026 is the new 2016 or something and then she was right Everybody started sending me pictures of where they were in 2016.

29:29.185 --> 29:39.218
I started getting them randomly on my phone people were sending me I'm not even on Instagram and I'm getting pictures on my phone 2016 2016 2016 2016 and I thought that's crazy.

29:39.238 --> 29:39.939
Where was I 2016?

29:40.059 --> 29:48.210
I pulled something up This is the first Sunday grand opening in our Ballantyne building in 2016

29:54.914 --> 30:02.418
And it was supposed to happen in 2014, but it was on a two-year delay.

30:02.498 --> 30:05.242
By the way, if you're in Kenya, you probably don't know what I'm talking about when I say Valentine.

30:05.502 --> 30:20.783
The building that I broadcast from, where we reach into your home, and where we reach into prisons, and where we send messages into rehabs, and where we send messages into hospital rooms, and where we send podcasts into cars of parents driving their kids around all day, and athletes that are getting all the ministry.

30:21.063 --> 30:28.754
It comes from right here at Valentine to all of our other campuses, and we were opening it 2016, and we were having the best time kind of.

30:28.774 --> 30:29.715
But show them the other picture.

30:30.216 --> 30:32.018
This is the one that was next to it on my phone.

30:33.506 --> 30:40.597
There's me and Holly, and she looks like blessing, and I look like pressure.

30:43.382 --> 30:43.963
Isn't that right?

30:45.124 --> 30:46.727
Would you say I captioned that correctly?

30:48.630 --> 30:51.715
Because for me, I was jet lagged that Sunday morning.

30:52.756 --> 30:54.760
For me, I had just gotten back from Australia.

30:55.901 --> 30:58.866
For me, the headlines were all about a potential

30:59.298 --> 31:01.100
place of civil unrest in our nation.

31:01.521 --> 31:05.666
For me, my best friend was getting fired from pastoring his church.

31:05.886 --> 31:15.178
Between the 930 and the 1130, I was talking to him on the phone before I came out to preach again, because I was scared about whether he was in a safe place emotionally or not.

31:16.800 --> 31:17.561
Now you understand.

31:17.581 --> 31:18.842
Put the picture back up again.

31:19.743 --> 31:19.924
Why?

31:20.004 --> 31:28.434
She's smiling, and I'm like… She's like, God is good all the time.

31:31.074 --> 31:32.296
She's like, this is an amazing day.

31:32.316 --> 31:40.427
Now, obviously that's just a really unfortunate capture of my face in that moment.

31:40.447 --> 31:41.508
I don't know why I was really thinking.

31:42.329 --> 31:45.474
We fired that photographer, by the way, captured that moment.

31:45.514 --> 31:45.894
I'm kidding.

31:47.336 --> 31:51.081
I just want to give you a visual for a moment here as we talk about Joseph and Ephraim and Manasseh.

31:52.163 --> 32:00.434
And as we talk about your life and as we talk about forgetting where you come from and when we talk about your past and when we talk about

32:00.802 --> 32:01.823
the things that you remember.

32:01.863 --> 32:15.198
And when we talk about the challenge that you're facing, remember, the people of Joseph, the tribes of Ephraim and Manasseh came to Joshua and said, it's too much and it's not enough.

32:16.580 --> 32:17.701
And Joshua said, it is enough.

32:18.823 --> 32:23.988
There is all of this territory that you were given, but it's forest territory.

32:25.550 --> 32:28.914
And it's covered not only in trees, but there are Canaanites that are there.

32:29.506 --> 32:33.031
which represent the enemies that you did not drive out of the land yet.

32:34.614 --> 32:41.485
God is giving you an inheritance, but to develop in that it's going to take two things, work and war.

32:43.868 --> 32:46.833
It's going to take work and it's going to take war.

32:48.756 --> 32:55.346
I heard an old self-motivation talk parable about a farmer who had a beautiful piece of property.

32:55.618 --> 32:56.839
It was so lush, man.

32:56.899 --> 33:00.783
The gardens were just beautiful and flourishing, and the cows were fat.

33:01.023 --> 33:05.227
The white gravel driveway was lined with the prettiest trees you ever saw.

33:05.668 --> 33:11.093
It didn't look like a new farm, but it looked like a love farm, a farm that had received a lot of attention.

33:12.094 --> 33:20.161
A preacher drove by the farm one day, and he was so absolutely enchanted with the farm that he had to meet the farmer.

33:20.862 --> 33:25.106
The farmer came over on the tractor and turned off the tractor for a moment and said,

33:25.186 --> 33:26.828
to the preacher, can I help you?"

33:27.709 --> 33:29.772
The preacher said, I was just admiring your property.

33:30.232 --> 33:33.657
What a beautiful piece of property the Lord gave you.

33:35.118 --> 33:38.543
The farmer said, Yes, it is very beautiful, and we're grateful.

33:39.404 --> 33:44.010
The preacher, you should have seen this place when the Lord had it all to himself.

33:48.896 --> 33:54.002
In other words, I worked this thing.

33:54.178 --> 33:57.382
the people that you're driving by and envying their life.

33:59.545 --> 34:01.667
They didn't just get that marriage.

34:02.168 --> 34:04.130
They didn't just get that body.

34:04.531 --> 34:07.294
They didn't just get that financial situation.

34:07.575 --> 34:09.838
They didn't just get that influence.

34:10.338 --> 34:14.303
They were in the field keeping sheep before Goliath ever showed up.

34:14.924 --> 34:16.626
They were developing it.

34:16.738 --> 34:22.986
And the question is, are you investing into what you inherited in your life?

34:23.567 --> 34:25.950
If it's a gift, are you investing in it?

34:26.230 --> 34:28.853
If it's a relationship, are you maintaining it?

34:29.274 --> 34:34.781
Are you working with what God gave you or simply complaining how it's not enough?

34:34.801 --> 34:36.643
Because I'm going to tell you, it is enough.

34:37.905 --> 34:38.706
It is enough.

34:39.330 --> 34:44.495
It just hasn't had the time yet in your life to develop into what it needs to be.

34:44.555 --> 34:47.067
So I came to declare a message today.

34:47.088 --> 34:48.434
It is enough.

34:48.610 --> 34:51.314
but it is going to take faith on your part.

34:51.875 --> 34:55.700
God is not simply going to drive out every enemy in your life.

34:56.241 --> 34:59.505
God is not simply going to chop down every tree in your life.

35:00.026 --> 35:04.392
God is not simply going to disrupt every bad habit in your life.

35:04.412 --> 35:05.814
We pray for deliverance.

35:06.175 --> 35:09.459
I believe in deliverance, but I also believe in support groups.

35:11.342 --> 35:13.485
I said I also believe in AA.

35:13.505 --> 35:17.170
I said I also believe in accountability.

35:17.826 --> 35:20.430
I said I also believe in Christian counseling.

35:21.050 --> 35:24.015
I said I also believe in starting to exercise.

35:24.635 --> 35:27.199
I said I also believe in app deletion.

35:27.700 --> 35:34.529
See, the thing about some of us is we are praying for peace in areas where we are unwilling to clear out trees.

35:36.271 --> 35:37.153
How can it grow?

35:37.173 --> 35:38.855
How can it grow?

35:38.895 --> 35:39.997
It has nowhere to grow.

35:40.017 --> 35:44.022
And the problem is not that I need more time.

35:44.363 --> 35:46.866
The problem is that I need more priorities.

35:47.650 --> 35:50.706
Because God gave me enough time for what he called me to do.

35:51.234 --> 35:57.780
So I declare in this year of my life, it's the year that I do what Joshua told the people of Joseph to do.

35:58.120 --> 35:58.761
Listen to this.

35:59.061 --> 36:00.302
He said, you have enough.

36:00.342 --> 36:01.143
Doesn't feel like enough.

36:01.383 --> 36:01.963
You have enough.

36:01.983 --> 36:02.884
Doesn't look like enough.

36:03.104 --> 36:04.305
There's all these trees.

36:04.586 --> 36:05.647
There's all these enemies.

36:05.907 --> 36:08.569
There's all these things that you have not confronted yet.

36:09.089 --> 36:14.975
But behind what you have been unwilling to confront is the answer to the prayer that you seek.

36:14.995 --> 36:18.177
I am preaching prophetically to somebody.

36:18.518 --> 36:20.339
Give me verse 17.

36:20.359 --> 36:21.220
Joshua said,

36:21.200 --> 36:26.908
To the people, to Ephraim and Manasseh, you are numerous and very powerful.

36:27.288 --> 36:32.896
You will have not only one allotment, you're two tribes, but you can have the forested country, too.

36:33.217 --> 36:34.939
There is more for you to enjoy.

36:35.260 --> 36:38.184
There is more for you to experience in God.

36:38.364 --> 36:40.407
You can be happy again.

36:40.707 --> 36:42.129
You can rejoice again.

36:42.490 --> 36:44.452
You can have meaning in your day again.

36:44.973 --> 36:48.498
You can have it if you clear it.

36:50.018 --> 36:51.540
Somebody shout, clear it.

36:52.782 --> 36:54.645
Speak that over your mind this year.

36:55.046 --> 36:55.567
Clear it.

36:55.908 --> 36:56.949
I gotta clear it.

36:57.270 --> 37:00.295
I'm praying for peace, but I'm not clearing my mind.

37:00.655 --> 37:08.187
How can I stuff my mind full of junk and then ask Jesus to fill the spaces already filled with junk?

37:08.207 --> 37:09.810
Somebody shout, clear it.

37:10.754 --> 37:15.626
It might have to be cleared in your life of some unproductive relationships this year.

37:15.686 --> 37:28.978
There are so many roots that can drink water in your yard, but any more than those roots and you are not going to have the rain you need for what God is planting, somebody shout, clear it!

37:29.250 --> 37:31.172
Don't even apologize to people.

37:31.453 --> 37:35.237
If you have to cut off some communication this year, that's all right.

37:35.518 --> 37:36.359
It's not rude.

37:36.619 --> 37:41.825
It's righteous because I have to clear it this year because God has more for me.

37:41.866 --> 37:46.351
I'm sorry I didn't get back with you.

37:46.651 --> 37:48.053
I have to get clear this year.

37:48.454 --> 37:50.256
I'm sorry I didn't snap you back.

37:50.556 --> 37:58.546
I have to get clear this year because what God gave me, what God is doing through me, what God promised me,

38:02.338 --> 38:02.719
Clear it.

38:06.023 --> 38:09.589
Clear your mind this year.

38:09.849 --> 38:13.915
This may be the season for you to stop focusing on what would have been.

38:14.276 --> 38:18.502
You are so full of regret that you cannot see what is right in front of you.

38:20.285 --> 38:20.705
Yes, Lord.

38:20.745 --> 38:21.747
Thank you for reminding me.

38:22.107 --> 38:24.751
The Word of the Lord, he says, you still can.

38:28.457 --> 38:29.298
You still can.

38:30.594 --> 38:34.379
Because the lie that starts to clutter up your mind is too late.

38:34.699 --> 38:36.561
Oh, look at the mistakes you made.

38:36.701 --> 38:39.465
How many of you have that going on in your mind in an area right now?

38:39.725 --> 38:42.589
Like if I would have just given it more attention, that may be true.

38:42.869 --> 38:44.491
You may have missed the opportunity.

38:44.551 --> 38:48.636
You may not have done it when you should have done it, but you still can.

38:50.398 --> 38:54.963
I wish I would have lived for God in college.

38:55.044 --> 38:56.706
Well, you are 79 now.

38:57.627 --> 39:00.370
You still can live for God and leave a legacy.

39:00.930 --> 39:02.652
Somebody shout, I still can.

39:04.174 --> 39:16.770
You can if you get clear, but if you stay in what it was in a previous season of your life, you will have more available to you and you will die for the lack of what Jesus died to put in your life.

39:18.952 --> 39:19.413
Clear it.

39:20.614 --> 39:21.115
Clear it.

39:22.397 --> 39:25.160
Tell the devil we are not having this conversation again.

39:26.241 --> 39:26.802
Clear it.

39:28.546 --> 39:30.511
Yes, I'm talking about your calendar.

39:30.772 --> 39:32.256
You need to clear it up a little bit.

39:33.359 --> 39:37.751
It's got a little too much stuff on it that you're doing to impress people, and it's not making an impact.

39:37.971 --> 39:38.352
Clear it.

39:40.077 --> 39:40.418
Clear it.

39:40.859 --> 39:43.506
Let me talk to a leader, because pastors watch me preach.

39:43.778 --> 39:51.467
Some of the people you are running around trying to please by preaching the sermons they want so bad are not supposed to be a part of your church in this season.

39:52.027 --> 39:58.554
If you don't stop preaching to the people who are threatening to leave, you cannot reach the people God has called you to reach, and they need Jesus.

39:58.674 --> 40:01.958
Clear it.

40:08.746 --> 40:12.690
This might be a prophetic word about your shopping cart on Amazon.

40:13.250 --> 40:14.893
You ain't buying none of it this year.

40:15.153 --> 40:16.635
We're getting out of debt this year.

40:17.096 --> 40:17.457
Okay.

40:21.383 --> 40:23.045
Lost all the shouts, LJ.

40:23.867 --> 40:25.930
No organ necessary on that point.

40:29.235 --> 40:32.881
And if you can clear it, you can conquer it.

40:32.901 --> 40:36.947
You remember I said we were two years late getting in this building?

40:37.948 --> 40:41.554
One of the reasons that we were so far behind getting in on this building

40:41.986 --> 40:53.180
